{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Power."},{"time":2000,"text":"That is the word that comes to mind."},{"time":4000,"text":"We're the new technologists."},{"time":6000,"text":"We have a lot of data, so we have a lot of power."},{"time":9000,"text":"How much power do we have?"},{"time":11000,"text":"Scene from a movie: \"Apocalypse Now\" -- great movie."},{"time":14000,"text":"We've got to get our hero, Captain Willard, to the mouth of the Nung River"},{"time":17000,"text":"so he can go pursue Colonel Kurtz."},{"time":19000,"text":"The way we're going to do this is fly him in and drop him off."},{"time":21000,"text":"So the scene:"},{"time":23000,"text":"the sky is filled with this fleet of helicopters carrying him in."},{"time":26000,"text":"And there's this loud, thrilling music in the background,"},{"time":28000,"text":"this wild music."},{"time":30000,"text":"♫ Dum da ta da dum ♫"},{"time":32000,"text":"♫ Dum da ta da dum ♫"},{"time":34000,"text":"♫ Da ta da da ♫"},{"time":37000,"text":"That's a lot of power."},{"time":39000,"text":"That's the kind of power I feel in this room."},{"time":41000,"text":"That's the kind of power we have"},{"time":43000,"text":"because of all of the data that we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"Let's take an example."},{"time":47000,"text":"What can we do"},{"time":49000,"text":"with just one person's data?"},{"time":52000,"text":"What can we do"},{"time":54000,"text":"with that guy's data?"},{"time":56000,"text":"I can look at your financial records."},{"time":58000,"text":"I can tell if you pay your bills on time."},{"time":60000,"text":"I know if you're good to give a loan to."},{"time":62000,"text":"I can look at your medical records; I can see if your pump is still pumping --"},{"time":65000,"text":"see if you're good to offer insurance to."},{"time":68000,"text":"I can look at your clicking patterns."},{"time":70000,"text":"When you come to my website, I actually know what you're going to do already"},{"time":73000,"text":"because I've seen you visit millions of websites before."},{"time":75000,"text":"And I'm sorry to tell you,"},{"time":77000,"text":"you're like a poker player, you have a tell."},{"time":79000,"text":"I can tell with data analysis what you're going to do"},{"time":81000,"text":"before you even do it."},{"time":83000,"text":"I know what you like. I know who you are,"},{"time":86000,"text":"and that's even before I look at your mail"},{"time":88000,"text":"or your phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"Those are the kinds of things we can do"},{"time":92000,"text":"with the data that we have."},{"time":95000,"text":"But I'm not actually here to talk about what we can do."},{"time":101000,"text":"I'm here to talk about what we should do."},{"time":105000,"text":"What's the right thing to do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"Now I see some puzzled looks"},{"time":111000,"text":"like, \"Why are you asking us what's the right thing to do?"},{"time":114000,"text":"We're just building this stuff. Somebody else is using it.\""},{"time":117000,"text":"Fair enough."},{"time":120000,"text":"But it brings me back."},{"time":122000,"text":"I think about World War II --"},{"time":124000,"text":"some of our great technologists then,"},{"time":126000,"text":"some of our great physicists,"},{"time":128000,"text":"studying nuclear fission and fusion --"},{"time":130000,"text":"just nuclear stuff."},{"time":132000,"text":"We gather together these physicists in Los Alamos"},{"time":135000,"text":"to see what they'll build."},{"time":138000,"text":"We want the people building the technology"},{"time":141000,"text":"thinking about what we should be doing with the technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"So what should we be doing with that guy's data?"},{"time":149000,"text":"Should we be collecting it, gathering it,"},{"time":152000,"text":"so we can make his online experience better?"},{"time":154000,"text":"So we can make money?"},{"time":156000,"text":"So we can protect ourselves"},{"time":158000,"text":"if he was up to no good?"},{"time":160000,"text":"Or should we respect his privacy,"},{"time":163000,"text":"protect his dignity and leave him alone?"},{"time":167000,"text":"Which one is it?"},{"time":170000,"text":"How should we figure it out?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"I know: crowdsource. Let's crowdsource this."},{"time":176000,"text":"So to get people warmed up,"},{"time":179000,"text":"let's start with an easy question --"},{"time":181000,"text":"something I'm sure everybody here has an opinion about:"},{"time":184000,"text":"iPhone versus Android."},{"time":186000,"text":"Let's do a show of hands -- iPhone."},{"time":189000,"text":"Uh huh."},{"time":191000,"text":"Android."},{"time":194000,"text":"You'd think with a bunch of smart people"},{"time":196000,"text":"we wouldn't be such suckers just for the pretty phones."},{"time":198000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":200000,"text":"Next question,"},{"time":202000,"text":"a little bit harder."},{"time":204000,"text":"Should we be collecting all of that guy's data"},{"time":206000,"text":"to make his experiences better"},{"time":208000,"text":"and to protect ourselves in case he's up to no good?"},{"time":211000,"text":"Or should we leave him alone?"},{"time":213000,"text":"Collect his data."},{"time":218000,"text":"Leave him alone."},{"time":221000,"text":"You're safe. It's fine."},{"time":223000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":225000,"text":"Okay, last question --"},{"time":227000,"text":"harder question --"},{"time":229000,"text":"when trying to evaluate"},{"time":232000,"text":"what we should do in this case,"},{"time":235000,"text":"should we use a Kantian deontological moral framework,"},{"time":239000,"text":"or should we use a Millian consequentialist one?"},{"time":244000,"text":"Kant."},{"time":247000,"text":"Mill."},{"time":250000,"text":"Not as many votes."},{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":255000,"text":"Yeah, that's a terrifying result."},{"time":259000,"text":"Terrifying, because we have stronger opinions"},{"time":263000,"text":"about our hand-held devices"},{"time":265000,"text":"than about the moral framework"},{"time":267000,"text":"we should use to guide our decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"How do we know what to do with all the power we have"},{"time":272000,"text":"if we don't have a moral framework?"},{"time":275000,"text":"We know more about mobile operating systems,"},{"time":278000,"text":"but what we really need is a moral operating system."},{"time":283000,"text":"What's a moral operating system?"},{"time":285000,"text":"We all know right and wrong, right?"},{"time":287000,"text":"You feel good when you do something right,"},{"time":289000,"text":"you feel bad when you do something wrong."},{"time":291000,"text":"Our parents teach us that: praise with the good, scold with the bad."},{"time":294000,"text":"But how do we figure out what's right and wrong?"},{"time":297000,"text":"And from day to day, we have the techniques that we use."},{"time":300000,"text":"Maybe we just follow our gut."},{"time":303000,"text":"Maybe we take a vote -- we crowdsource."},{"time":306000,"text":"Or maybe we punt --"},{"time":308000,"text":"ask the legal department, see what they say."},{"time":311000,"text":"In other words, it's kind of random,"},{"time":313000,"text":"kind of ad hoc,"},{"time":315000,"text":"how we figure out what we should do."},{"time":318000,"text":"And maybe, if we want to be on surer footing,"},{"time":321000,"text":"what we really want is a moral framework that will help guide us there,"},{"time":324000,"text":"that will tell us what kinds of things are right and wrong in the first place,"},{"time":327000,"text":"and how would we know in a given situation what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"So let's get a moral framework."},{"time":333000,"text":"We're numbers people, living by numbers."},{"time":336000,"text":"How can we use numbers"},{"time":338000,"text":"as the basis for a moral framework?"},{"time":341000,"text":"I know a guy who did exactly that."},{"time":344000,"text":"A brilliant guy --"},{"time":347000,"text":"he's been dead 2,500 years."},{"time":350000,"text":"Plato, that's right."},{"time":352000,"text":"Remember him -- old philosopher?"},{"time":354000,"text":"You were sleeping during that class."},{"time":357000,"text":"And Plato, he had a lot of the same concerns that we did."},{"time":359000,"text":"He was worried about right and wrong."},{"time":361000,"text":"He wanted to know what is just."},{"time":363000,"text":"But he was worried that all we seem to be doing"},{"time":365000,"text":"is trading opinions about this."},{"time":367000,"text":"He says something's just. She says something else is just."},{"time":370000,"text":"It's kind of convincing when he talks and when she talks too."},{"time":372000,"text":"I'm just going back and forth; I'm not getting anywhere."},{"time":374000,"text":"I don't want opinions; I want knowledge."},{"time":377000,"text":"I want to know the truth about justice --"},{"time":380000,"text":"like we have truths in math."},{"time":383000,"text":"In math, we know the objective facts."},{"time":386000,"text":"Take a number, any number -- two."},{"time":388000,"text":"Favorite number. I love that number."},{"time":390000,"text":"There are truths about two."},{"time":392000,"text":"If you've got two of something,"},{"time":394000,"text":"you add two more, you get four."},{"time":396000,"text":"That's true no matter what thing you're talking about."},{"time":398000,"text":"It's an objective truth about the form of two,"},{"time":400000,"text":"the abstract form."},{"time":402000,"text":"When you have two of anything -- two eyes, two ears, two noses,"},{"time":404000,"text":"just two protrusions --"},{"time":406000,"text":"those all partake of the form of two."},{"time":409000,"text":"They all participate in the truths that two has."},{"time":413000,"text":"They all have two-ness in them."},{"time":415000,"text":"And therefore, it's not a matter of opinion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"What if, Plato thought,"},{"time":420000,"text":"ethics was like math?"},{"time":422000,"text":"What if there were a pure form of justice?"},{"time":425000,"text":"What if there are truths about justice,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and you could just look around in this world"},{"time":429000,"text":"and see which things participated,"},{"time":431000,"text":"partook of that form of justice?"},{"time":434000,"text":"Then you would know what was really just and what wasn't."},{"time":437000,"text":"It wouldn't be a matter"},{"time":439000,"text":"of just opinion or just appearances."},{"time":442000,"text":"That's a stunning vision."},{"time":444000,"text":"I mean, think about that. How grand. How ambitious."},{"time":447000,"text":"That's as ambitious as we are."},{"time":449000,"text":"He wants to solve ethics."},{"time":451000,"text":"He wants objective truths."},{"time":453000,"text":"If you think that way,"},{"time":456000,"text":"you have a Platonist moral framework."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"If you don't think that way,"},{"time":461000,"text":"well, you have a lot of company in the history of Western philosophy,"},{"time":463000,"text":"because the tidy idea, you know, people criticized it."},{"time":466000,"text":"Aristotle, in particular, he was not amused."},{"time":469000,"text":"He thought it was impractical."},{"time":472000,"text":"Aristotle said, \"We should seek only so much precision in each subject"},{"time":476000,"text":"as that subject allows.\""},{"time":478000,"text":"Aristotle thought ethics wasn't a lot like math."},{"time":481000,"text":"He thought ethics was a matter of making decisions in the here-and-now"},{"time":484000,"text":"using our best judgment"},{"time":486000,"text":"to find the right path."},{"time":488000,"text":"If you think that, Plato's not your guy."},{"time":490000,"text":"But don't give up."},{"time":492000,"text":"Maybe there's another way"},{"time":494000,"text":"that we can use numbers as the basis of our moral framework."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"How about this:"},{"time":500000,"text":"What if in any situation you could just calculate,"},{"time":503000,"text":"look at the choices,"},{"time":505000,"text":"measure out which one's better and know what to do?"},{"time":508000,"text":"That sound familiar?"},{"time":510000,"text":"That's a utilitarian moral framework."},{"time":513000,"text":"John Stuart Mill was a great advocate of this --"},{"time":515000,"text":"nice guy besides --"},{"time":517000,"text":"and only been dead 200 years."},{"time":519000,"text":"So basis of utilitarianism --"},{"time":521000,"text":"I'm sure you're familiar at least."},{"time":523000,"text":"The three people who voted for Mill before are familiar with this."},{"time":525000,"text":"But here's the way it works."},{"time":527000,"text":"What if morals, what if what makes something moral"},{"time":530000,"text":"is just a matter of if it maximizes pleasure"},{"time":532000,"text":"and minimizes pain?"},{"time":534000,"text":"It does something intrinsic to the act."},{"time":537000,"text":"It's not like its relation to some abstract form."},{"time":539000,"text":"It's just a matter of the consequences."},{"time":541000,"text":"You just look at the consequences"},{"time":543000,"text":"and see if, overall, it's for the good or for the worse."},{"time":545000,"text":"That would be simple. Then we know what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547000,"text":"Let's take an example."},{"time":549000,"text":"Suppose I go up"},{"time":551000,"text":"and I say, \"I'm going to take your phone.\""},{"time":553000,"text":"Not just because it rang earlier,"},{"time":555000,"text":"but I'm going to take it because I made a little calculation."},{"time":558000,"text":"I thought, that guy looks suspicious."},{"time":561000,"text":"And what if he's been sending little messages to Bin Laden's hideout --"},{"time":564000,"text":"or whoever took over after Bin Laden --"},{"time":566000,"text":"and he's actually like a terrorist, a sleeper cell."},{"time":569000,"text":"I'm going to find that out, and when I find that out,"},{"time":572000,"text":"I'm going to prevent a huge amount of damage that he could cause."},{"time":575000,"text":"That has a very high utility to prevent that damage."},{"time":578000,"text":"And compared to the little pain that it's going to cause --"},{"time":580000,"text":"because it's going to be embarrassing when I'm looking on his phone"},{"time":582000,"text":"and seeing that he has a Farmville problem and that whole bit --"},{"time":585000,"text":"that's overwhelmed"},{"time":588000,"text":"by the value of looking at the phone."},{"time":590000,"text":"If you feel that way,"},{"time":592000,"text":"that's a utilitarian choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"But maybe you don't feel that way either."},{"time":598000,"text":"Maybe you think, it's his phone."},{"time":600000,"text":"It's wrong to take his phone"},{"time":602000,"text":"because he's a person"},{"time":604000,"text":"and he has rights and he has dignity,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and we can't just interfere with that."},{"time":608000,"text":"He has autonomy."},{"time":610000,"text":"It doesn't matter what the calculations are."},{"time":612000,"text":"There are things that are intrinsically wrong --"},{"time":615000,"text":"like lying is wrong,"},{"time":617000,"text":"like torturing innocent children is wrong."},{"time":620000,"text":"Kant was very good on this point,"},{"time":623000,"text":"and he said it a little better than I'll say it."},{"time":625000,"text":"He said we should use our reason"},{"time":627000,"text":"to figure out the rules by which we should guide our conduct,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and then it is our duty to follow those rules."},{"time":633000,"text":"It's not a matter of calculation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"So let's stop."},{"time":638000,"text":"We're right in the thick of it, this philosophical thicket."},{"time":641000,"text":"And this goes on for thousands of years,"},{"time":644000,"text":"because these are hard questions,"},{"time":646000,"text":"and I've only got 15 minutes."},{"time":648000,"text":"So let's cut to the chase."},{"time":650000,"text":"How should we be making our decisions?"},{"time":654000,"text":"Is it Plato, is it Aristotle, is it Kant, is it Mill?"},{"time":657000,"text":"What should we be doing? What's the answer?"},{"time":659000,"text":"What's the formula that we can use in any situation"},{"time":662000,"text":"to determine what we should do,"},{"time":664000,"text":"whether we should use that guy's data or not?"},{"time":666000,"text":"What's the formula?"},{"time":670000,"text":"There's not a formula."},{"time":674000,"text":"There's not a simple answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"Ethics is hard."},{"time":679000,"text":"Ethics requires thinking."},{"time":683000,"text":"And that's uncomfortable."},{"time":685000,"text":"I know; I spent a lot of my career"},{"time":687000,"text":"in artificial intelligence,"},{"time":689000,"text":"trying to build machines that could do some of this thinking for us,"},{"time":692000,"text":"that could give us answers."},{"time":694000,"text":"But they can't."},{"time":696000,"text":"You can't just take human thinking"},{"time":698000,"text":"and put it into a machine."},{"time":700000,"text":"We're the ones who have to do it."},{"time":703000,"text":"Happily, we're not machines, and we can do it."},{"time":706000,"text":"Not only can we think,"},{"time":708000,"text":"we must."},{"time":710000,"text":"Hannah Arendt said,"},{"time":712000,"text":"\"The sad truth"},{"time":714000,"text":"is that most evil done in this world"},{"time":716000,"text":"is not done by people"},{"time":718000,"text":"who choose to be evil."},{"time":720000,"text":"It arises from not thinking.\""},{"time":723000,"text":"That's what she called the \"banality of evil.\""},{"time":727000,"text":"And the response to that"},{"time":729000,"text":"is that we demand the exercise of thinking"},{"time":731000,"text":"from every sane person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"So let's do that. Let's think."},{"time":736000,"text":"In fact, let's start right now."},{"time":739000,"text":"Every person in this room do this:"},{"time":742000,"text":"think of the last time you had a decision to make"},{"time":745000,"text":"where you were worried to do the right thing,"},{"time":747000,"text":"where you wondered, \"What should I be doing?\""},{"time":749000,"text":"Bring that to mind,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and now reflect on that"},{"time":753000,"text":"and say, \"How did I come up that decision?"},{"time":756000,"text":"What did I do? Did I follow my gut?"},{"time":759000,"text":"Did I have somebody vote on it? Or did I punt to legal?\""},{"time":761000,"text":"Or now we have a few more choices."},{"time":764000,"text":"\"Did I evaluate what would be the highest pleasure"},{"time":766000,"text":"like Mill would?"},{"time":768000,"text":"Or like Kant, did I use reason to figure out what was intrinsically right?\""},{"time":771000,"text":"Think about it. Really bring it to mind. This is important."},{"time":774000,"text":"It is so important"},{"time":776000,"text":"we are going to spend 30 seconds of valuable TEDTalk time"},{"time":778000,"text":"doing nothing but thinking about this."},{"time":780000,"text":"Are you ready? Go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"Stop. Good work."},{"time":801000,"text":"What you just did,"},{"time":803000,"text":"that's the first step towards taking responsibility"},{"time":805000,"text":"for what we should do with all of our power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"Now the next step -- try this."},{"time":814000,"text":"Go find a friend and explain to them"},{"time":816000,"text":"how you made that decision."},{"time":818000,"text":"Not right now. Wait till I finish talking."},{"time":820000,"text":"Do it over lunch."},{"time":822000,"text":"And don't just find another technologist friend;"},{"time":825000,"text":"find somebody different than you."},{"time":827000,"text":"Find an artist or a writer --"},{"time":829000,"text":"or, heaven forbid, find a philosopher and talk to them."},{"time":832000,"text":"In fact, find somebody from the humanities."},{"time":834000,"text":"Why? Because they think about problems"},{"time":836000,"text":"differently than we do as technologists."},{"time":838000,"text":"Just a few days ago, right across the street from here,"},{"time":841000,"text":"there was hundreds of people gathered together."},{"time":843000,"text":"It was technologists and humanists"},{"time":845000,"text":"at that big BiblioTech Conference."},{"time":847000,"text":"And they gathered together"},{"time":849000,"text":"because the technologists wanted to learn"},{"time":851000,"text":"what it would be like to think from a humanities perspective."},{"time":854000,"text":"You have someone from Google"},{"time":856000,"text":"talking to someone who does comparative literature."},{"time":858000,"text":"You're thinking about the relevance of 17th century French theater --"},{"time":861000,"text":"how does that bear upon venture capital?"},{"time":863000,"text":"Well that's interesting. That's a different way of thinking."},{"time":866000,"text":"And when you think in that way,"},{"time":868000,"text":"you become more sensitive to the human considerations,"},{"time":871000,"text":"which are crucial to making ethical decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"So imagine that right now"},{"time":876000,"text":"you went and you found your musician friend."},{"time":878000,"text":"And you're telling him what we're talking about,"},{"time":881000,"text":"about our whole data revolution and all this --"},{"time":883000,"text":"maybe even hum a few bars of our theme music."},{"time":885000,"text":"♫ Dum ta da da dum dum ta da da dum ♫"},{"time":888000,"text":"Well, your musician friend will stop you and say,"},{"time":890000,"text":"\"You know, the theme music"},{"time":892000,"text":"for your data revolution,"},{"time":894000,"text":"that's an opera, that's Wagner."},{"time":896000,"text":"It's based on Norse legend."},{"time":898000,"text":"It's Gods and mythical creatures"},{"time":900000,"text":"fighting over magical jewelry.\""},{"time":904000,"text":"That's interesting."},{"time":907000,"text":"Now it's also a beautiful opera,"},{"time":910000,"text":"and we're moved by that opera."},{"time":913000,"text":"We're moved because it's about the battle"},{"time":915000,"text":"between good and evil,"},{"time":917000,"text":"about right and wrong."},{"time":919000,"text":"And we care about right and wrong."},{"time":921000,"text":"We care what happens in that opera."},{"time":924000,"text":"We care what happens in \"Apocalypse Now.\""},{"time":927000,"text":"And we certainly care"},{"time":929000,"text":"what happens with our technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"We have so much power today,"},{"time":933000,"text":"it is up to us to figure out what to do,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and that's the good news."},{"time":938000,"text":"We're the ones writing this opera."},{"time":941000,"text":"This is our movie."},{"time":943000,"text":"We figure out what will happen with this technology."},{"time":946000,"text":"We determine how this will all end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}